awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/resolved.png","name":"Resolved","id":"5","statusCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/3","id":3,"key":"done","colorName":"green","name":"Done"}},"components":[{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10012","id":"10012","name":"Properties Service"}],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"description":"Services are difficult to configure using automation because they can become available inconsistently during initialization.  For example, blockstoragemanager and objectstorage provider require storage component to be in ready state but sometimes this can take longer especially depending on the storage backend used.  We canâ€™t rely on a status command to show us accurate service or property state, and therefore instead must wait an indeterminate period of time before setting the next configuration value.  This seems like a good area for improvement, not just for our install process, but for users to know that the product is enterprise quality.\r\n \r\nA prime example of this is EUCA-11684, which while old, is still occasionally a problem, requiring a retry of calyptos provision.\r\n\r\nSimilarly, properties should have consistent states so that they can be queried and a documented state should be returned.\r\n","customfield_13000":null,"customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfield_11500":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_10005":null,"customfield_10401":null,"customfield_10600":null,"customfield_12900":null,"attachment":[],"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"summary":"Service and property lifecycle standardization","creator":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=mbacchi","name":"mbacchi","key":"mbacchi","accountId":"557058:d650aabc-f00c-4262-93a9-7799945b8eed","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/24b916c1f